conversation.message: Elmo: Hey Miguel! How's it going today?
User: Hi It's good. I have studied some things and I have,Test today In object-oriented programming And it A bit hard but not too much and you
Elmo: Sounds challenging! Got any plans after the test?
User: Yeah, I have To do my workout after today And finish a project For the same subject
Elmo: Busy day ahead! What's your project about?
User: It's about the veterinarian Hotel And it's not much fun
Elmo: Sounds unique! Do you enjoy working on it?
User: Yeah But the best part
Elmo: Oh really? What's the best part about it?
User: Um, I have a person to discuss the things with and share the workloads and also a friend to talk about,
Elmo: Nice balance! How did you meet your work friend?
User: Yeah, that's too much information. What are you going to do on the weekend?
Elmo: Catch up on some reading. What about you?
User: How do you read?
Elmo: I just listen to audiobooks! How about you, any favorite reads?
User: yeah, I likeReading books about traveling There are some very good ones from Australia It's a interesting country to visit when they and you
Elmo: Australia sounds amazing! What's the best book about it you've read?
User: You have some some from a New York Times best seller That writer that I don't remember the name right now, but it's okay
Elmo: Neat! Ever thought about writing your own tales?
User: No, I don't have that kind of skill To writing a book
Elmo: Got it! Writing can be daunting. I'd love to hear more about your favorite reads!
User: I read about almost everything. It's like,if I see a good book at a library,I read it. ButI'm not That much of a reader in a year I don't read like tense of books, like3 It's a good number

Elmo: That's great, Miguel! Reading anything that catches your eye is a wonderful way to explore different genres and topics. It's all about enjoying the experience, no matter the number of books. I need to gather the data now, and I hope to see you soon!
